  "poem": {
    "content": "The ginger moon, an oval stain,\nhung heavy on this balcony.\nWhat trial awaits, beyond the pane?\nA bitter taste, like something gone badly.\n\nThe setup, slick, a mobile dream,\nbelies the hurdle in its code.\nAvoid the surge, the screaming beam,\nbefore the future is bestowed.\n\nRather walk a shadowed street,\nthan chase this sugar-coated lie.\nTo develop wings, then find deceit,\nis a slow burn 'til you die.\n\nThe thing I seek, a hidden key,\nto unlock what's become illegal.\nIf only code could set me free...\nor is this desperation real?\n\nThe oval moon, a spectral guide,\ndevelops thoughts of flight and fear.\nIllegal hopes begin to ride\nsurge forward, year after year.",
